WPK Birthday Marked in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 19 (KCNA) -- Meetings, lectures, photo exhibitions and film shows took place at the head offices of the Communist Party of Tajikistan, the Workers' Party of Mexico and the Pakistan Socialist Party from Sept. 29 to Oct. 5 on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 Displayed in the venues of those functions were photos showing the exploits President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il performed in founding the Party and strengthening it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the film show watched a Korean film "For the Liberation of the Country". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 S. Shabdolov, chairman of the CPT, addressing a meeting, noted that the WPK has covered a road of victory for the last six decades under the wise leadership of the President and Kim Jong Il, overcoming all sorts of ordeals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Arturo Lopez, member of the National Executive Committee of the Workers' Party of Mexico, in his speech at a meeting said that the 60 year-long history of the WPK is the history of revolutionary activities of the President and Kim Jong Il, adding that the foundation of the WPK was a historic event which brought about a radical turn in carving out the destiny of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 C. R. Aslam, president of the Pakistan Socialist Party, in a lecture titled "The eternal party of Comrade Kim Il Sung" said that as it is led by Kim Jong Il boundlessly faithful to the idea and cause of Kim Il Sung, the WPK has demonstrated its might as the dignified party of the President.
 Meanwhile, round-table talks took place in Syria on Oct. 5 and in the Czech Republic on Oct. 12 on the occasions of the 60th birthday of the WPK and the 25th anniversary of the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo.

Rodong Sinmun on Significant Celebration of WPK Birthday 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 19 (KCNA) -- A number of grand events held in celebration of the 60th anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea in an unprecedented elated political atmosphere clearly proved the unbounded reverence and loyalty of the servicepersons and people of the DPRK to President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il and the great might of the unbreakable single-minded unity of the entire Party and army and all the people around the headquarters of the revolution, says Rodong Sinmun Wednesday in a signed article.
 The grand festival in October was a grand political festival as it strikingly manifested the unshakable faith and will of the servicepersons and people to uphold the President's idea and cause with loyalty, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The national meeting, the grand gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang", the military parade, the evening gala and torchlight procession held in the presence of  Kim Jong Il to mark the 60th anniversary of the WPK fully represented the glorious history of the WPK and the Korean revolution associated with the august name of  Kim Il Sung. They also reflected the WPK's unshakable faith and will to accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche that started in the forests of Mt. Paektu under the uplifted banner of the red flag associated with the whole life of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The single-minded unity of the Korean people has reached the present highest level because they acclaimed the President as their leader and the proud feature and might of their unity would be unthinkable without this great national fortune and glory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The October festival was also a manifestation of the single-minded unity of the servicepersons and people of the DPRK around the headquarters of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Labor achievements contributed to the anniversary such as the Taean Friendship Glass Factory, the Paekma-Cholsan Waterway, the Dam of the Nyongwon Power Station, the Kumjingang Hungbong Youth Power Station and proud achievements made on all fronts for building a great prosperous powerful nation fully reflected their unshakable faith that they would certainly emerge victorious as long as they are under the leadership of  Kim Jong Il and the revolutionary stamina that they are ready to go through thick and thin and make anything regarded impossible possible true to his intention and determination. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The grand festival also strikingly demonstrated the spirit of Songun Korea advancing thanks to the might of strong revolutionary armed forces that have inherited the tradition of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK could celebrate the anniversary as the most auspicious festival in the world in terms of its scope and content and its political and ideological value thanks to this most mighty Songun revolutionary unity and this provided an opportunity of demonstrating the perfect organization and strong discipline and unity and cohesion of our revolutionary ranks, the article concludes.

Rodong Sinmun on Idea of "By Our Nation Itself" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 19 (KCNA) -- No matter how hard the outside forces may work to check the movement of the Korean nation for independent reunification, they can never stop the Korean nation from advancing in the idea of "By our nation itself", says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 The might of unity which the Korean nation is cementing in every way is an invincible might guaranteeing a victory in the cause of national reunification, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National reunification is the unanimous desire of all the fellow countrymen and the law-governing requirement of national development.
 As long as the outsiders' moves against reunification continue, the Korean nation's cause of reunification can never be smooth.
 The idea of "By our nation itself" helps the Korean nation aspiring after peace and reunification pool their efforts against the aggressive outsiders and promote its unity on a nation-wide scale and encourages the cause of national reunification with the might of its great unity to advance victoriously.
 The idea helps members of the nation have feelings  of love for the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The united power of the nation rallied in the idea of "By our nation itself" is the might of the driving force and patriotism which guarantees a victory of independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic June 15 joint declaration provided the Korean nation with the idea of "By our nation itself", a powerful ideological and mental weapon for accomplishing the cause of national reunification. All the fellow countrymen at home and abroad have since conducted a vigorous movement for reunification on the basis of the idea of "By our nation itself" and in this process the might of the idea has been fully demonstrated.
 Though the outsiders are running amuck to obliterate the cause of national reunification, the Korean nation advancing under the banner of "By our nation itself" will always emerge victorious.

Kim Yong Nam Meets Nigerian Government Delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 19 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, met and had a friendly talk with the visiting Nigerian government delegation headed by Mallam Nasir Ahmad El-Rufai, minister of Federal Capital Territory, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Wednesday.
 Present there were Choe Jong Gon, minister of City Management, Kim Hyong Jun, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, and Sule Buba, Nigerian ambassador e. p. to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The head of the delegation said that President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il performed undying exploits for the country's sovereignty and happiness of its people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the belief that the friendly relations between the two countries would as ever grow stronger, he hoped that Korea would be surely reunified under the banner of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration.

Traitorous Diatribe of Dong-A Ilbo Blasted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 19 (KCNA) -- The Secretariat of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland Wednesday issued information bulletin No. 908 vehemently denouncing the south Korean Dong-A Ilbo for its traitorous diatribe. 
 It said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An editorial of the paper dated Oct. 15 found fault with the south Korean Uri Party's proposal for exchange between the ruling parties of the south and the north. It asserted that "there was concern about the possibility to stir up ideological disarmament in the south Korean society" and "it was an appeasement policy toward the north stepped up under the slogan of independence and by our nation itself." It went the lengths of labeling the north "a principal enemy" and attacking the north, branding the Workers' Party of Korea as "an enemy-benefiting organization under the existing law".
 What the newspaper said in its editorial was an unpardonable provocation to the north and a blatant challenge to the desire and wishes of the Koreans for national reconciliation and unity, peace and reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This was nothing but the last resort of the pro-U.S. conservative forces opposed to reunification to chill the desire for achieving independent reunification through alliance with the north which has become a trend of the times in south Korea and divert it in a bid to prevent their foundation from collapsing. 
 The information bulletin recalled that this newspaper has long thrown a stumbling block in the way of the progressive development of the south Korean society and the improvement of the inter-Korean relations by slandering the dignified political system in the north and decrying the movement of the south Korean people for independence, democracy and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It continued: Though five years have passed since the publication of the June 15 joint declaration, Dong-A Ilbo remains unchanged in its treacherous behavior of advocating sycophancy and treachery and confrontation with compatriots. It would be well advised to drop its old habit of inciting inter-Korean confrontation.
